SUMMARY:Spring Native Plant Sale
DESCRIPTION:9 a.m. – 12 p.m.: Pre-registration required. One registration allows all people in your vehicle to access to the plant sale. Registration details will be e-mailed to our monthly e-newsletter recipients. Want to join this list? Sign up here \n12-2 p.m.: Open shopping\, no registration required \nJoin the North Carolina Botanical Garden and other local native plant nurseries for our annual Spring Native Plant Sale! Shop from a great selection of plants and support small businesses. \nGrowing Wild Nursery\, Mellow Marsh Farm\, Carolina Habitats (formerly Dirtbag Gardens)\, and the North Carolina Botanical Garden will be offering a wide variety of southeastern native perennials\, vines\, shrubs\, trees\, grasses\, and carnivorous plants. \n\nTips:\nPayment Methods\nYou must pay for your plants at each vendor this year. There will NOT be a consolidated check-out area. Please be sure to purchase your plants BEFORE walking away from each vendor’s area. All vendors will accept credit cards. Some vendors will accept additional forms of payment – please ask them for clarification BEFORE loading up. \nB.Y.O.-Cart\nIf you’re planning to get more plants than you can easily carry in a tray\, you may wish to bring your own cart or wagon. (We have some here\, but not enough for everyone.) \nPlants\nWe will not be publishing a plant list in advance for this sale\, but between the four vendors there will be a wide variety of southeastern native perennials\, grasses\, ferns\, vines\, shrubs\, and trees for sale. \nRain or Shine\nThe sale will be rain or shine: we recommend sunscreen if it’s sunny or a rain jacket if it’s rainy! \nAgain\, thanks for your interest in the sale and native plants!
URL:https://ncbg.unc.edu/event/spring-native-plant-sale/
LOCATION:North Carolina Botanical Garden\, 100 Old Mason Farm Road\, Chapel Hill\, NC\, 27517\, United States
CATEGORIES:Special Events
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://ncbg.unc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/963/2019/07/DSC_0271.jpg
